					xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
					xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
					xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					xmlns:ns3="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
					xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
					xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">

	<refnamediv>
		<refname>imrotate</refname>

		<refpurpose>Rotate Image</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>

		<synopsis> dst=imrotate(source,angle);</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection>

		<title>Parameters</title>

		<variablelist>                                                                            
			<varlistentry><term>source:</term>
				<listitem><para>list of pixels of input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>      
                         <varlistentry><term>angle:</term>        
				<listitem><para> angle by which image is to be rotated.</para></listitem></varlistentry>     
                         <varlistentry><term>dst</term>        
				<listitem><para> list of pixels of output rotated image returned by function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>     
                    
		</variablelist>

	</refsection>



	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para>Rotate Image </para>
	
		<para>The function rotates image by the angle specified by angle parameter in function.</para>

		<para>It is expected that the user input should be a list of pixels of source image which can RGB image or gray scale image and the function will return list of pixels of rotated image.Value of angle can be negative or positive depending whether we want image to be rotated in clockwise or anticlockwise direction.
		</para>
		
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Examples</title>

		<programlisting role="example">b=rgb2gray(a)</programlisting>
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Authors</title>

		<simplelist type="vert">
			<member>Priyanka Hiranandani</member>
		</simplelist>
	</refsection>
</refentry>

